                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Rectangular block of Botticino stone, broken at bottom. Originally intended as a funerary altar, but was hollowed out to make a baptismal font. The side faces are decorated in bas-relief with images of two Erotes, they are holding torches, and one is also holding a garland. The three worked faces of the stone are framed by ornamental motifs, including palmettes and laurel branches.</p>
